995,http://www.armslist.com/posts/3509995,For Sale:  Saiga 12ga 922(r) - Get it before it's banned!,"Anywhere, Denver, Colorado","$ 1,500","Listed On: Thursday, September 18, 2014",Shotguns,Saiga                                                                                ,12 Gauge                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Shotgun,"Versatility was the primary objective in modifying this 922r-compliant Saiga 12 shotgun; the project was conceived as an answer to the question of what kind of weapon would be ideal in a ""Walking Dead"" world. It would need to be something with proven track record for reliability with plenty of replacement parts. A ""zombie apocalypse"" weapon would need to be quick and easy to reload, with a minimum amount of time between shots, so semiautomatic and magazine-fed. It would also need to be adaptable to hunting, defense, breaching and assault situations, which means support for a variety of loads and projectile types.

A shotgun is capable of these things far more effectively than a rifle or a handgun. And Kalashnikov action weapons are known the world over for their resilience against the elements, with the AK-47 being the most widely-proliferated firearm in the world. Hence, the Saiga 12ga - a semiautomatic, magazine-fed Kalashnikov action shotgun based on the AK-47 platform - was an ideal candidate.

The shotgun pictured has been modified with a US-made fire control group, an upgraded V-plug from MD Arms (to allow fine-grained control of the weapon's behavior with different loads), as well as coming equipped with a high-quality, milled aluminum quad rail, ergonomic pistol grip and folding, extendable stock. This configuration expands the versatility of the weapon by providing a secure platform for scopes, lasers, flashlights, red dot sights, and more. All of these parts were made in the USA and are of the highest quality.

Additionally, the stock finish from IZHMASH (the manufacturer of the Saiga 12) is a cheap paint that easily scratches and can be rubbed off by a paper towel. To protect against the elements, this shotgun has been sandblasted and professionally treated with Norrell's Moly Resin, which provides excellent rust and corrosion protection. This self-lubricating finish also meets Mil-spec for: 60-day seawater immersion; immersion in acids, powder solvents, paint removers, bore cleaners; and accelerated salt spray tests equivalent to 30 years marine environment. It is flat black in appearance, to match the furniture attached.

And if that's not enough to entice you into stocking up for facing hordes of the undead, I'll even throw in 5 ""Dragon's Breath"" shells (where legally permissible). These specially-designed shells spew a 70ft fireball of blazing hot magnesium pellets, so you can engage the walkers with an AK-47 flamethrowing assault shotgun in style.
** GET IT BEFORE IT'S BANNED **

This summer, the Obama Administration banned import of Russian firearms as part of a sanctions package in response to the invasion of the Ukraine. As a result, Kalashnikov Concern (formerly Izhmash), maker of the Saiga 12ga, and similar Kalashnikov-action firearms, can no longer be imported by dealers in the United States. Private ownership and transfer is legal... for now. This rifle represents one of the last lots legally imported into the U.S. for conversion into a tactical configuration. Grab it before it's too late!
** NOTE: EOTECH NOT INCLUDED **"
